03/05/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Ahmet Davutoglu announced on Monday (May 2nd) that Turkey is temporarily closing its embassy in Tripoli because of the aggravated security situation in the city. 
Embassy staff has been evacuated to Tunisia. 
Davutoglu added that the decision was made after weekend attacks against the embassies of Great Britain and Italy. 
He stressed that this does not mean Turkey is halting its diplomatic efforts to restore peace in Libya. 
(Vatan - 03/05/11; Haber 3, Hurriyet - 02/05/11)
